headline: Notice Letter to Pulitzer Prize Board
body_text: The Russia, Russia, Russia hoax has been totally debunked. The fake news media covered it incorrectly—reporting exactly the opposite of what actually happened.Yet, the Pulitzer Board has not rescinded the prizes they awarded for reporting that was inaccurate, inept, and corrupt.In order to restore the credibility of the Pulitzer Prizes, the Pulitzer Board should take away prizes from all who got it wrong.Additionally, it would be appropriate to award new prizes to all those who got it right. Read my Notice Letter to Pulitzer Prize Board here.
